  "P1.NMM-1": {
    sufficiency: {
      clause: "EN 18031-1 §6.7.1",
      purpose_en: "The purpose of this assessment case is the functional validation of the appropriateness of the Network\nMonitoring Mechanisms described in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM]. The assessment verifies whether the traffic\nbetween networks (which is controlled or processed by the network equipment) is monitored and\nanalysed to mitigate the risk related to security assets and network assets in the networks documented\nin [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM.NetworkEquipment].",
      units_en: "For each network monitoring mechanism documented in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM]:\n[AU.NMM-1.GTPFiltering]: When the implementation is based on [IC.NMM-1.GTPFiltering] functionally\nconfirm that:\n— GTP messages are monitored by the network equipment; and\n— GTP messages sender authorization is verified by the network equipment; and\n— the network equipment is able to define and apply rules for the different GTP messages.\n[AU.NMM-1.IPPacketFiltering]: When the implementation is based on [IC.NMM-1.IPPacketFiltering]\nfunctionally confirm that:\ninternet protocol packets such as ICMP and ARP are revealed and monitored by the network equipment;\nand\n— a simulated ICMP based DoS attack is detected; and\n— a simulated ARP based DoS attack is detected; and\n— measure to limit the effect of such DoS attacks are put in place.\n[AU.NMM-1.Generic]: When the implementation is based on [IC.NMM-1.Generic] functionally confirm\nthat:\nAssessment of traffic between networks processed, controlled, or served by the network equipment.\n— Assess traffic between networks processed by the network equipment, to reveal processed\nprotocol types via network analysing tools, use the information in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM.NetworkEquipment] as a guidance; and\n— assess if the revealed traffic and protocol types which are part of the traffic between networks\nprocessed by the network equipment are documented in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM.NetworkEquipment], in relation to the risk for security assets and network assets\nprocessed, controlled or served by the network equipment between networks.\nSimulate the in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM] described conditions to trigger the related monitoring e.g., via\ngenerating malformed messages or messages in a very high cadence (e.g., via fuzzing), use [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM] as guidance.\nAssess if the in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM] described behaviour or output is generated as documented, use\nnetwork equipment manual or design documentation as guidance.",
      verdict_en: "The verdict PASS for the assessment case is assigned if for each network monitoring mechanism\ndocumented in [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM] the confirmations in the implementation category dependent\nassessment unit are successful.\nThe verdict FAIL for the assessment case is assigned if for a network monitoring mechanism documented\nin [E.Info.NMM-1.NMM] a confirmation in the implementation category dependent assessment unit is not\nsuccessful.\nThe verdict NOT APPLICABLE for the assessment case is assigned otherwise.",
    },
  },
