      purpose_en: "The purpose of this assessment case is the functional validation of the appropriateness of the Traffic\nControl Mechanisms described in [E.Info.TCM-1.TCM]. The assessment verifies whether the traffic\nforwarded by the network equipment to a network is controlled to avoid compromising or harm the\nnetwork assets and security assets in the networks which are controlled or served by the network\nequipment.",
      units_en: "For each traffic control mechanism documented in [E.Info.TCM-1.TCM]:\n[AU.TCM-1.DatagramRules]: If the implementation is based on [IC.TCM-1.DatagramRules], functionally\nconfirm that:\n— datagrams are monitored by the network equipment; and\n— a simulated anomalous patterns and malicious traffic is detected and discarded or blocked;\nand\n— datagrams with not authorized source or address destination are detected and discarded or\nblocked.\n[AU.TCM-1.TrafficSeparation]: If the implementation is based on [IC.TCM-1.TrafficSeparation],\nfunctionally confirm that:\n— for each different network domain, traffic forwarding between the network domains is not\nallowed by the network equipment.\n[AU.TCM-1.Generic]: If the implementation is based on [IC.TCM-1.Generic], functionally confirm that:\n— the traffic forwarded by the network equipment is controlled and the controls are\nimplemented as described in [E.Info.TCM-1.TCM].",
